                <h2>Adding Value to Everything You Do</h2>
                <p>Wendorf Beward &amp; Partners has developed a reputation for producing creative, implementable solutions to difficult problems. Setting up systems, getting things done on time and on budget, providing professional training and measuring improvement requires real life experience in a public agency, as well as academic and analytical skills. At Wendorf Beward &amp; Partners, we have the skills and knowledge to transform and add value to critical systems.</p>
                <p><strong>Setting the Standards and Measuring Results</strong><br>Wendorf Beward &amp; Partners has provided performance improvement development and rollout for various public service activities. A key component of the development is to set goals, efficiencies, effectiveness and productivity standards. Data sets, transaction analysis, cost allocations and other details are all part of the standards. Management must review and observe these standards to understand if the standard has been met and if there is a positive or negative deviation, understand the &ldquo;why&rdquo; to make significant positive change better or to change the negative progress to a positive impact.</p>
                <p><strong>Getting More from What&rsquo;s There</strong><br>In addition to developing performance improvements for clients, Wendorf Beward &amp; Partners has also provided the back check on programs not initiated by Wendorf Beward &amp; Partners to note standards and deviations along with recommendations for positive improvement to those programs.</p>
                <p><strong>How A Major City Made Major Improvements</strong><br>Wendorf Beward &amp; Partners implemented Service Level Agreements (SLA) at the departmental level in the 7th largest city in the United States, the City of San Antonio. External SLAs were published in the annual budget and Internal SLAs were used as leading indicators for daily, weekly and monthly management review and action. Performance measures for program management in the consulting role were developed and utilized for continuous review and formal monthly project reviews. Standards of performance were established and reported in a formal manner for budget, scope and schedule control. Accountability ran as a &ldquo;thread&rdquo; throughout the high performance organization.</p>
                <p>Operational improvements in public service delivery occurred including:</p>
